Error Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.DbUpdateConcurrencyException: &#39;The database operation was expected to affect 1 row(s), but actually affected 0 row(s); data may have been modified or deleted since entities were loaded. See http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=527962 for information on understanding and handling optimistic concurrency exceptions.&#39; Code before foreach (var entity in entities)
{
ctx.Entry(entity).State = EntityState.Modified;
}
ctx.SaveChanges(); The problem was that some of the entities, that were residing in memory, were modified and saved in the database while their copy in memory were not updated.

